WARRI – Former Chairman of Ethiope West Local Government Area in Delta State, Dr Wilson Omene has urged Nigerians to keep hope alive by main­taining the commitment and zeal to lift the country of its present social and economic predicaments. Dr Omene, a marine ex­pert, described the dreaded COVID-19 pandemic as the greatest global challenge that has taken the lives of millions of humans in recent time, saying “the pandemic was made worse in Nigeria by over 20 per cent inflation in the prices of food and ser­vices, strikes in the public sector and Endsars protests.” On the forthcoming lo­cal government elections in some states, he lamented “Politicians in Nigeria have no regard for voters at the lo­cal government level. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! “At the local government level in Nigeria, the politi­cians in high places pre-se­lect their chairmanship can­didates from the aspirants even before the elections are held as they have nothing to do with the voters.” Dr Omene called on politi­cians of the All Progressives Congress, APC, to “shun greed and self-centeredness and ensure that they field credible, experienced and in­tellectually sound candidates in the politics of Delta State in 2023, particularly at the governorship level.” SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION